// Module sdktest is the SDK-conformance harness: a SEPARATE Go module that
// imports the public sandbox SDK (client, client/cred) exactly the way an
// external consumer does. Because it sits outside the main module, the Go
// compiler enforces here what it cannot enforce in-module: that the exported
// API never requires naming an internal/... type, and that every pinned
// signature keeps compiling. `just sdk-conformance` (part of `just check`)
// runs it; see surface_test.go / conformance_test.go.
module github.com/cullenmcdermott/sandbox/sdktest

go 1.26.2

require (
	charm.land/bubbletea/v2 v2.0.7
	charm.land/lipgloss/v2 v2.0.4
	github.com/charmbracelet/x/ansi v0.11.7
	github.com/cullenmcdermott/sandbox v0.0.0
)

